{
    "thig13.4:0.1_0": "Second: Mallikā",
    "thig13.4:0.2_0": "The Book of the Twenties",
    "thig13.4:0.3_0": "Sundarī",
    "thig13.4:1.1_0": "“Before, when your children passed away,",
    "thig13.4:1.2_0": "you would expose them to be eaten.",
    "thig13.4:1.3_0": "All day and all night",
    "thig13.4:1.4_0": "you’d be racked with despair.",
    "thig13.4:10.1_0": "suffering that arises,",
    "thig13.4:10.2_0": "for going beyond suffering,",
    "thig13.4:10.3_0": "the noble eightfold path,",
    "thig13.4:10.4_0": "the stilling of suffering.",
    "thig13.4:11.1_0": "Having understood the true teaching there,",
    "thig13.4:11.2_0": "he chose to go forth.",
    "thig13.4:11.3_0": "Three days later",
    "thig13.4:11.4_0": "Sujāta realized the three knowledges.",
    "thig13.4:12.1_0": "“Please, charioteer, go;",
    "thig13.4:12.2_0": "take back this carriage.",
    "thig13.4:12.3_0": "Bidding my brahmin lady good health, say:",
    "thig13.4:12.4_0": "‘The brahmin has now gone forth.",
    "thig13.4:12.5_0": "Three days later",
    "thig13.4:12.6_0": "Sujāta realized the three knowledges.’”",
    "thig13.4:13.1_0": "Then taking the carriage,",
    "thig13.4:13.2_0": "along with a thousand coins, the charioteer",
    "thig13.4:13.3_0": "bade the brahmin lady good health, and said:",
    "thig13.4:13.4_0": "“The brahmin has now gone forth.",
    "thig13.4:13.5_0": "Three days later",
    "thig13.4:13.6_0": "Sujāta realized the three knowledges.”",
    "thig13.4:14.1_0": "Hearing that the brahmin had the three knowledges, the lady replied:",
    "thig13.4:14.2_0": "along with a thousand coins, the charioteer",
    "thig13.4:14.3_0": "O charioteer, along with 1000 coins,",
    "thig13.4:14.4_0": "and a full bowl as a gift.”",
    "thig13.4:15.1_0": "“Keep the horse and carriage, lady,",
    "thig13.4:15.2_0": "along with the thousand coins.",
    "thig13.4:15.3_0": "I too shall go forth,",
    "thig13.4:15.4_0": "for the Buddha’s teaching.",
    "thig13.4:16.1_0": "“Like a gem with jeweled earrings,",
    "thig13.4:16.2_0": "such opulent domestic wealth:",
    "thig13.4:16.3_0": "having given it up, your father went forth,",
    "thig13.4:16.4_0": "enjoy these riches Sundarī,",
    "thig13.4:16.5_0": "you are the family heir.”",
    "thig13.4:17.1_0": "“Like a gem with jeweled earrings,",
    "thig13.4:17.2_0": "such delightful domestic wealth:",
    "thig13.4:17.3_0": "having given it up, my father went forth,",
    "thig13.4:17.4_0": "racked by grief for his son.",
    "thig13.4:17.5_0": "I too shall go forth,",
    "thig13.4:17.6_0": "racked by grief for my brother.”",
    "thig13.4:18.1_0": "“Sundarī, may the wish you desire",
    "thig13.4:18.2_0": "you’ve swept away.",
    "thig13.4:18.3_0": "makes sure, non-humans or caught up in fire,",
    "thig13.4:18.4_0": "the root of a tree as lodging,",
    "thig13.4:18.5_0": "make do with these,",
    "thig13.4:18.6_0": "free of defilements regarding the next life.”",
    "thig13.4:19.1_0": "“Ma’am, while I am still a trainee nun,",
    "thig13.4:19.2_0": "my clairvoyance was clarified,",
    "thig13.4:19.3_0": "and I knew my past lives,",
    "thig13.4:19.4_0": "I can recollect.",
    "thig13.4:2.1_0": "Today, brahmin lady, you have exposed",
    "thig13.4:2.2_0": "seven children in all to be eaten;",
    "thig13.4:2.3_0": "Chewned by discontent,",
    "thig13.4:2.4_0": "you’re not so filled with despair?”",
    "thig13.4:20.1_0": "Relying on a fine lady like you,",
    "thig13.4:20.2_0": "a senior nun who beautifies the Sangha,",
    "thig13.4:20.3_0": "I attained the three knowledges",
    "thig13.4:20.4_0": "and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions.”",
    "thig13.4:21.1_0": "Give me permission ma’am,",
    "thig13.4:21.2_0": "I wish to go to Sāvatthī,",
    "thig13.4:21.3_0": "where I shall roar my lion’s roar",
    "thig13.4:21.4_0": "before the best of Buddhas.”",
    "thig13.4:22.1_0": "“Sundarī, see the Teacher!",
    "thig13.4:22.2_0": "Golden colored, golden skinned,",
    "thig13.4:22.3_0": "Tamer of the untamed,",
    "thig13.4:22.4_0": "the Awakened One who fears nothing from any quarter.”",
    "thig13.4:23.1_0": "“See Sundarī coming,",
    "thig13.4:23.2_0": "liberated, free of attachments,",
    "thig13.4:23.3_0": "desireless, detached,",
    "thig13.4:23.4_0": "her task completed, without defilements.”",
    "thig13.4:24.1_0": "“Having set forth from Bārāṇasī",
    "thig13.4:24.2_0": "and come to your presence, great hero,",
    "thig13.4:24.3_0": "your disciple Sundarī",
    "thig13.4:24.4_0": "bows at your feet.",
    "thig13.4:25.1_0": "You are the Teacher, the teacher!",
    "thig13.4:25.2_0": "I am your rightful daughter, brahmin,",
    "thig13.4:25.3_0": "born of your mouth.",
    "thig13.4:25.4_0": "the task completed, without defilements.”",
    "thig13.4:26.1_0": "“Then welcome, good lady,",
    "thig13.4:26.2_0": "you’re by no means unwelcome.",
    "thig13.4:26.3_0": "For this is how the tamed come",
    "thig13.4:26.4_0": "bowing at the Teacher’s feet;",
    "thig13.4:26.5_0": "desireless, detached,",
    "thig13.4:26.6_0": "the task completed, without defilements.”",
    "thig13.4:27.1_0": "... Sundarī ...",
    "thig13.4:3.1_0": "“Many hundreds of sons,",
    "thig13.4:3.2_0": "hundreds of family circles,",
    "thig13.4:3.3_0": "both mine and yours, brahmin,",
    "thig13.4:3.4_0": "have been eaten in the past.",
    "thig13.4:4.1_0": "Having known the escape",
    "thig13.4:4.2_0": "of rebirth and death,",
    "thig13.4:4.3_0": "I neither grieve nor lament,",
    "thig13.4:4.4_0": "nor do I despair.”",
    "thig13.4:5.1_0": "“Wow, Vaseṭṭhī, the words you speak",
    "thig13.4:5.2_0": "that you say such things?",
    "thig13.4:5.3_0": "You understand the teaching and practice accordingly",
    "thig13.4:5.4_0": "that you say these things?”",
    "thig13.4:6.1_0": "“Brahmin, the Awakened One",
    "thig13.4:6.2_0": "at the city of Mithilā,",
    "thig13.4:6.3_0": "for giving up all suffering;",
    "thig13.4:6.4_0": "may abandon all suffering.",
    "thig13.4:7.1_0": "After hearing the perfected one’s teaching,",
    "thig13.4:7.2_0": "brahmin, which is free of all attachments,",
    "thig13.4:7.3_0": "having understood the true teaching there,",
    "thig13.4:7.4_0": "I’ve swept away grief for children.”",
    "thig13.4:8.1_0": "“I too shall go",
    "thig13.4:8.2_0": "at the city of Mithilā,",
    "thig13.4:8.3_0": "Hopefully the Buddha may release me",
    "thig13.4:8.4_0": "from all suffering.”",
    "thig13.4:9.1_0": "The brahmin saw the Buddha,",
    "thig13.4:9.2_0": "liberated, free of attachments,",
    "thig13.4:9.3_0": "He taught him the Dhamma,",
    "thig13.4:9.4_0": "the sage gone beyond suffering:"
}